description: The Ocala Stage Race returns for the 6th year. This year we move one week earlier to allow riders to make final preparations for the Junior Nationals and DairyLand. We will use the same three courses we have over the past couple years. We use the same start finish line each stage and even allow camping overnight at the race venue.  We will offer racing for all categories and age groups and will feature separate womens and juniors races.
course: The rolling courses of Marion County\'s horse country makes for some of the coolest race courses in the state. TopView Sports has listened to what racers want and have asked for.  We bring the only two Road Race weekend in the state.
registration: Registration will open 1 hour to prior to the first race each day. It will close 15 minutes before each category starts. This race will use TopView Sports Tiered Race Pricing. This means that racers will be able to register for only $25 per road stage and $20 for the TT by registering 30 days prior to race day online or mailing in a registration form with Standard Athlete Release..
notes: All USAC rules apply. Promoter reserves the right to combine or cancel races if minimum fields are not met. Prize money will be awarded ONLY for the OVERALL General Class. There will be NO stage prizes or medals for any categories. Riders are welcome to participate in individual stages for upgrade points and FPS Points and glory but since this is a Timed Stage Race the only prize money will be for the OVERALL.
directions: Same race address for all three stages.

title: 8 Hours of Pine Log
description:
For the 11th Annual Pine Log race, we\'re temporailiy departing from the beloved 12 Hour format to an 8 Hour race due to unforseen restrictions of the event location conflicts and manpower. We\'ll be back to 12 Hours next year, but this year will be a true test of our participants pain threshold as they\'ll have to sprint for all 8 hours to win this event!


We\'ve organized our race categores to faciliate this all-out format: Men and Women\'s Solo 4 Hours, Co-Ed/Men\'s/Women\'s 2 Person 8 Hour Relay , and the Open 8 Hour Relay (Only restrictions are 4 person max).


Additionally, the start time has been moved later in the day to allow for twilight riding.


The Metric Century will include a map, SAG vehicles, a reststop and a t-shirt.
registration:
http://www.active.com/cycling/ebro-fl/8-hours-of-pine-log-2012

Same day registration closes 30 minutes before start.
directions: From Hwy 79, turn West onto Environmental Rd. at Pine Log State Forest. Take first right (North) onto Long Leaf Rd. Continue to trail head and park.
